etermine what music to perform when multiple versions of an opera exist? What are the implications of omitting passages from an opera in a performance? In addition to vexing questions such as these, Gossett also tackles issues of ornamentation and transposition in vocal style, the matters of translation and adaptation, and even aspects of stage direction and set design. Throughout this extensive and passionate work, Gossett enlivens his history with reports from his own experiences with major opera companies at venues ranging from the Metropolitan and Santa Fe operas to the Rossini Opera Festival at Pesaro. The result is a book that will enthrall both aficionados of Italian opera and newcomers seeking a reliable introduction to it—in all its incomparable grandeur and timeless allure.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 7aMUSIC / General.2bisacsh  aopera music, musical criticism, composers, personal experiences, performing arts, divas, singing, operatic performances, musicians, scandals, italy, stage production, theater, social history, 19th century, scores, scholars, conductors, performers, critical edition, ornamentation, vocal style, adaptation, translation, set design, direction, metropolitan, pesaro, rossini festival, bellini, donizetti, scandinavia, instruments, semiramide, summer festivals.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311063538640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226304885423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226304885/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles